Class PaymentData

java.lang.Object
  dk.dibs.android.library.PaymentData
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
PreAuthorizationPaymentData, PreAuthPurchasePaymentData, PurchasePaymentData, TicketPurchasePaymentData
public abstract class PaymentData
extends Object
implements Serializable

Base class for generating payment window data.

You should be using the concrete subclasses of this class, that conforms to the payment flow you need.

See Also:
PurchasePaymentData, PreAuthorizationPaymentData, TicketPurchasePaymentData, PreAuthPurchasePaymentData, Serialized Form

getCancelUrl

public URL getCancelUrl()

setCancelUrl

public void setCancelUrl(URL cancelUrl)
URL to be loaded by payment window if payment was cancelled.

It is optional to give a cancel URL, but if it has been set, the payment window will try to load it, in the case where a payment is cancelled. In the case of cancelled payment, if a cancel URL has been set, both PaymentResultListener.cancelUrlLoaded() and PaymentResultListener.paymentCancelled(java.util.Map) are called.

Parameters:
cancelUrl - the URL for cancel of payment
